s3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m1115 xc5 h4 y1a23 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What question did Jesus ask the scribes? Verse 16. </div><div class="t ma2 x64 h4 y2040 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t ma97 xc5 h4 y1cfa ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What explanation did one of the multitude give? Verses 17, </div><div class="t mdb0 xc5 h4 y1af1 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">18. Note 1. </div><div class="t m1cd x64 h4 y17f1 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m6dc xc5 h4 y17f1 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did Jesus rebuke the unbelief of the people? What did </div><div class="t mdad xc5 h4 y129f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">He ask them to do? Verse 19. </div><div class="t m1d0 x64 h4 y1b64 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m18c xc5 h4 y1b64 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">When the boy was brought into the presence of Jesus, what </div><div class="t m165a xc5 h4 y1cff ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">did the spirit do that controlled him? Verse </div><div class="t mffb x4f h34 y16cd ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">20. </div><div class="t m8bb xc6 h4 y16cd ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Note </div><div class="t m231 xb6 h34 y16cd ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m1d2 x64 h4 yc23 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7. </div><div class="t m1f57 xc5 h4 yc23 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What question did Jesus ask the father? What was the </div><div class="t m8c6 xc5 h4 y1eda ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">answer? Verse 21. </div><div class="t m1d5 x64 h4 y1c0c ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. </div><div class="t mdfe xc5 h4 y1655 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">By what means had this evil spirit tried to destroy the boy? </div><div class="t m6d xc5 h4 y1e48 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">For what did the father earnestly plead? Verse </div><div class="t m840 x4d h34 y1e48 ff4 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">22. </div><div class="t m127 x64 h4 y184f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">9. </div><div class="t md9b xc5 h4 y184f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did JeSus seek to strengthen the faith of the father? </div>